      "span_text": "Representation of formant movement was significantly correlated with identification accuracy, but duration was only weakly correlated with identification performance in quiet, indicating that F1/F2 target frequencies contribute more to individual differences in L2 vowel identification in English, and that duration is a secondary cue that can have value in noisy conditions when the formant information is less clear [CITATION_1] ."
